.TH "str_field_delimit" 9 "str_field_delimit" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
str_field_delimit \- delimit a string based on a separator char.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "char *" str_field_delimit
.BI "(char **str "  ","
.BI "char separator "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "str" 12
the pointer to the string to delimit.
.IP "separator" 12
char that delimits the field
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Find a \fIseparator\fP and replace it by '\0'.
Remove leading and trailing spaces.
Return the remainder string after the \fIseparator\fP.
